{"types":[{"section":"\n{{fr-verb}}\n\n# to [[want]] {{+obj|fr|:de}}\n#: {{uxi|fr|Est-ce que tu '''as envie''' de fraises, par hasard ?|Would you '''like''' some strawberries, by any chance?}}\n# to [[want]], to [[desire]] (sexually) {{+obj|fr|:de}}\n#: {{uxi|fr|J''''ai envie''' de toi.|I '''want''' you.}}\n# to [[feel like]], to [[want]] to {{+obj|fr|:de}}\n#: {{uxi|fr|J''''ai envie''' de baiser.|I '''wanna''' fuck.}}\n#: {{uxi|fr|Je n''''ai''' pas '''envie''' de danser.|I don't '''feel like''' dancing.}}\n# to [[feel]] an [[urge]] {{+obj|fr|:de<to>}}\n#: {{uxi|fr|J''''ai envie''' de vomir.|I '''wanna''' puke.}}\n#: {{uxi|fr|J''''ai envie''' de chier.|I '''gotta''' take a shit.}}\n# {{lb|fr|by ellipsis}} to need to use the toilet\n#: {{uxi|fr|Maman, j''''ai envie'''!|Mommy, I '''have to go'''!}}\n\n====Usage notes====\n* Even though {{m|fr|envie}} is a noun, it can take an adverb: {{m|fr||j'en ai très envie|I want it a lot}}, and likewise for ''avoir trop envie, avoir tellement envie'', and the like. This usage, frowned upon in the past, is now perfectly standard; conversely, an adjectival modifier ({{m|fr||j'en ai grande envie}}) sounds dated. The same is true of the other French nouns that are used with ''avoir'' and without an article to indicate states or emotions:  {{m|fr|avoir faim}}, {{m|fr|avoir soif}}, {{m|fr|avoir chaud}}, {{m|fr|avoir froid}}, {{m|fr|avoir mal}}, {{m|fr|avoir honte}}, {{m|fr|avoir peur}}, {{m|fr|avoir besoin}}, {{m|fr|avoir raison}}, {{m|fr|avoir tort}}, {{m|fr|avoir sommeil}}, {{m|fr|avoir marre}}.","alt":[],"syn":[],"type":"verb","forms":[{"mod":"inf","aux":["avoir"],"pronom":false}],"html":"<p><span class=\"headword-line\"><strong class=\"Latn headword\" lang=\"fr\"><a href=\"/wiki/avoir#French\" title=\"avoir\">avoir</a> <a href=\"/wiki/envie#French\" title=\"envie\">envie</a></strong></span>\n</p><ol><li>to <a href=\"/wiki/want\" title=\"want\">want</a> <style data-mw-deduplicate=\"TemplateStyles:r80655919\">.mw-parser-output .object-usage-tag{font-style:italic}.mw-parser-output .deprecated{color:olivedrab}</style>[<i>with</i> <b class=\"Latn\" lang=\"fr\"><a href=\"/wiki/de#French\" title=\"de\">de</a></b>]\n<dl><dd><span class=\"h-usage-example\"><i class=\"Latn mention e-example\" lang=\"fr\">Est-ce que tu <b>as envie</b> de fraises, par hasard ?</i> ― <span class=\"e-translation\">Would you <b>like</b> some strawberries, by any chance?</span></span></dd></dl></li>\n<li>to <a href=\"/wiki/want\" title=\"want\">want</a>, to <a href=\"/wiki/desire\" title=\"desire\">desire</a> (sexually) <link rel=\"mw-deduplicated-inline-style\" href=\"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r80655919\">[<i>with</i> <b class=\"Latn\" lang=\"fr\"><a href=\"/wiki/de#French\" title=\"de\">de</a></b>]\n<dl><dd><span class=\"h-usage-example\"><i class=\"Latn mention e-example\" lang=\"fr\">J'<b>ai envie</b> de toi.</i> ― <span class=\"e-translation\">I <b>want</b> you.</span></span></dd></dl></li>\n<li>to <a href=\"/wiki/feel_like\" title=\"feel like\">feel like</a>, to <a href=\"/wiki/want\" title=\"want\">want</a> to <link rel=\"mw-deduplicated-inline-style\" href=\"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r80655919\">[<i>with</i> <b class=\"Latn\" lang=\"fr\"><a href=\"/wiki/de#French\" title=\"de\">de</a></b>]\n<dl><dd><span class=\"h-usage-example\"><i class=\"Latn mention e-example\" lang=\"fr\">J'<b>ai envie</b> de baiser.</i> ― <span class=\"e-translation\">I <b>wanna</b> fuck.</span></span></dd>\n<dd><span class=\"h-usage-example\"><i class=\"Latn mention e-example\" lang=\"fr\">Je n'<b>ai</b> pas <b>envie</b> de danser.</i> ― <span class=\"e-translation\">I don't <b>feel like</b> dancing.</span></span></dd></dl></li>\n<li>to <a href=\"/wiki/feel\" title=\"feel\">feel</a> an <a href=\"/wiki/urge\" title=\"urge\">urge</a> <link rel=\"mw-deduplicated-inline-style\" href=\"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r80655919\">[<i>with</i> <b class=\"Latn\" lang=\"fr\"><a href=\"/wiki/de#French\" title=\"de\">de</a></b> <small>‘to’</small>]\n<dl><dd><span class=\"h-usage-example\"><i class=\"Latn mention e-example\" lang=\"fr\">J'<b>ai envie</b> de vomir.</i> ― <span class=\"e-translation\">I <b>wanna</b> puke.</span></span></dd>\n<dd><span class=\"h-usage-example\"><i class=\"Latn mention e-example\" lang=\"fr\">J'<b>ai envie</b> de chier.</i> ― <span class=\"e-translation\">I <b>gotta</b> take a shit.</span></span></dd></dl></li>\n<li><span class=\"usage-label-sense\"><span class=\"ib-brac label-brac\">(</span><span class=\"ib-content label-content\"><a href=\"/wiki/Appendix:Glossary#ellipsis\" title=\"Appendix:Glossary\">by ellipsis</a></span><span class=\"ib-brac label-brac\">)</span></span> to need to use the toilet\n<dl><dd><span class=\"h-usage-example\"><i class=\"Latn mention e-example\" lang=\"fr\">Maman, j'<b>ai envie</b>!</i> ― <span class=\"e-translation\">Mommy, I <b>have to go</b>!</span></span></dd></dl></li></ol><div class=\"mw-heading mw-heading4\"><h4 id=\"Usage_notes\">Usage notes</h4><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=avoir_envie&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: Usage notes\"><span>edit</span></a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></div><ul><li>Even though <i class=\"Latn mention\" lang=\"fr\"><a href=\"/wiki/envie#French\" title=\"envie\">envie</a></i> is a noun, it can take an adverb: <i class=\"Latn mention\" lang=\"fr\">j'en ai très envie</i> <span class=\"mention-gloss-paren annotation-paren\">(</span><span class=\"mention-gloss-double-quote\">“</span><span class=\"mention-gloss\">I want it a lot</span><span class=\"mention-gloss-double-quote\">”</span><span class=\"mention-gloss-paren annotation-paren\">)</span>, and likewise for <i>avoir trop envie, avoir tellement envie</i>, and the like. This usage, frowned upon in the past, is now perfectly standard; conversely, an adjectival modifier (<i class=\"Latn mention\" lang=\"fr\">j'en ai grande envie</i>) sounds dated. The same is true of the other French nouns that are used with <i>avoir</i> and without an article to indicate states or emotions:  <i class=\"Latn mention\" lang=\"fr\"><a href=\"/wiki/avoir_faim#French\" title=\"avoir faim\">avoir faim</a></i>, <i class=\"Latn mention\" lang=\"fr\"><a href=\"/wiki/avoir_soif#French\" title=\"avoir soif\">avoir soif</a></i>, <i class=\"Latn mention\" lang=\"fr\"><a href=\"/wiki/avoir_chaud#French\" title=\"avoir chaud\">avoir chaud</a></i>, <i class=\"Latn mention\" lang=\"fr\"><a href=\"/wiki/avoir_froid#French\" title=\"avoir froid\">avoir froid</a></i>, <i class=\"Latn mention\" lang=\"fr\"><a href=\"/wiki/avoir_mal#French\" title=\"avoir mal\">avoir mal</a></i>, <i class=\"Latn mention\" lang=\"fr\"><a href=\"/wiki/avoir_honte#French\" title=\"avoir honte\">avoir honte</a></i>, <i class=\"Latn mention\" lang=\"fr\"><a href=\"/wiki/avoir_peur#French\" title=\"avoir peur\">avoir peur</a></i>, <i class=\"Latn mention\" lang=\"fr\"><a href=\"/wiki/avoir_besoin#French\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"avoir besoin\">avoir besoin</a></i>, <i class=\"Latn mention\" lang=\"fr\"><a href=\"/wiki/avoir_raison#French\" title=\"avoir raison\">avoir raison</a></i>, <i class=\"Latn mention\" lang=\"fr\"><a href=\"/wiki/avoir_tort#French\" title=\"avoir tort\">avoir tort</a></i>, <i class=\"Latn mention\" lang=\"fr\"><a href=\"/wiki/avoir_sommeil#French\" title=\"avoir sommeil\">avoir sommeil</a></i>, <i class=\"Latn mention\" lang=\"fr\"><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=avoir_marre&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"avoir marre (page does not exist)\">avoir marre</a></i>.</li></ul>","trans":["to want .mw-parser-output .object-usage-tag{font-style:italic}.mw-parser-output .deprecated{color:olivedrab}","to want, to desire","to feel like, to want to","to feel an urge","to need to use the toilet"]}],"title":"avoir envie","id":"1795585","audios":[{"name":"LL-Q150 (fra)-LoquaxFR-avoir envie.wav","url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/3/3d/L